    {
      "id": "PopularPost280391",
      "post_content": "This is not even worth a card, just add a creature with battlecry, it's not hard, seriously. This is not what any deck wants, even if it was put on a stick. The only constructed play this card will see is as a proxy. It's barely even playable in limited ... Now if it was +2+0, that would be a limited card! But, no, no, too broken. \\*sigh\\* They should have tried to make it at least playable as a 13th pick. Drafting red in m13 had 3 easy to get chase cards. [Goblin Arsonist](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Goblin Arsonist), [Krenko's Command](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Krenko's Command), and [Arms Dealer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arms Dealer), if you curved correctly into that, it was game over. This card just makes no sense. Maybe run this with [Odric, Master Tactician](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Odric, Master Tactician) in limited? I don't know, I'm trying here ... this card is terrible.  \n  \n0.5/5",
      "posted_by": "Ligerman30",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost280391\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">This is not even worth a card, just add a creature with battlecry, it's not hard, seriously.  This is not what any deck wants, even if it was put on a stick.  The only constructed play this card will see is as a proxy.  It's barely even playable in limited ...  Now if it was +2+0, that would be a limited card!  But, no, no, too broken.  *sigh*  They should have tried to make it at least playable as a 13th pick.  Drafting red in m13 had 3 easy to get chase cards.  <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Goblin Arsonist\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Goblin Arsonist\">Goblin Arsonist</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Krenko's Command\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Krenko's Command\">Krenko's Command</a>, and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arms Dealer\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arms Dealer\">Arms Dealer</a>, if you curved correctly into that, it was game over.  This card just makes no sense.  Maybe run this with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Odric, Master Tactician\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Odric, Master Tactician\">Odric, Master Tactician</a> in limited?  I don't know, I'm trying here ... this card is terrible.<br/><br/>0.5/5</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '280391'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n              